00:56:56.500 --> 00:56:59.710 align:middle line:84%
And people ask-- why
is it so universal?

00:56:59.710 --> 00:57:01.990 align:middle line:84%
Think about what your
teeth are used for.

00:57:01.990 --> 00:57:04.320 align:middle line:84%
They're used to feed
you and to protect you.

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:06.820 align:middle line:84%
Now, we think if someone were
to come in here and attack us,

00:57:06.820 --> 00:57:08.270 align:middle line:90%
we'd fight with our fists.

00:57:08.270 --> 00:57:10.780 align:middle line:84%
Back in the day,
you would bite them.

00:57:10.780 --> 00:57:13.222 align:middle line:10%
So actually, with our
teeth falling out, often we

00:57:13.222 --> 00:57:15.430 align:middle line:10%
have that dream when we're
feeling like we can't feed

00:57:15.430 --> 00:57:19.000 align:middle line:10%
ourselves, money worries, or
we can't protect ourselves,

00:57:19.000 --> 00:57:21.820 align:middle line:10%
relationship worries,
socioeconomic worries.

00:57:21.820 --> 00:57:23.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you can get
lucid in a dream

00:57:23.470 --> 00:57:24.910 align:middle line:84%
where your teeth
are falling out,

00:57:24.910 --> 00:57:27.310 align:middle line:90%
you can actually ask the dream--

00:57:27.310 --> 00:57:30.190 align:middle line:84%
what does my teeth
falling out represent?

00:57:30.190 --> 00:57:31.750 align:middle line:90%
And the dream will respond.

00:57:31.750 --> 00:57:34.460 align:middle line:84%
A dream character could
literally walk in and say--

00:57:34.460 --> 00:57:36.610 align:middle line:84%
dude, you've got to get
your finances in order.

00:57:36.610 --> 00:57:37.812 align:middle line:90%
We're struggling here.

00:57:37.812 --> 00:57:38.770 align:middle line:90%
I'm trying to help you.

00:57:38.770 --> 00:57:40.870 align:middle line:84%
But you need to sort
this out in real life.

00:57:40.870 --> 00:57:44.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing what you can
get from the dream if you ask.

00:57:44.500 --> 00:57:46.020 align:middle line:90%
It seems so simple.

00:57:46.020 --> 00:57:48.400 align:middle line:84%
But just two weeks ago,
I was feeling stuck.

00:57:48.400 --> 00:57:50.500 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I had so
many projects that had

00:57:50.500 --> 00:57:51.870 align:middle line:90%
come to an end in this year.

00:57:51.870 --> 00:57:53.610 align:middle line:90%
What was the next big project?

00:57:53.610 --> 00:57:54.410 align:middle line:90%
So I got lucid.

00:57:54.410 --> 00:57:55.840 align:middle line:90%
And I called out to the dream--

00:57:55.840 --> 00:57:58.330 align:middle line:90%
show me what I need to see.

00:57:58.330 --> 00:57:59.890 align:middle line:90%
Not show me what I want to see.

00:57:59.890 --> 00:58:01.500 align:middle line:90%
Show me what I need to see.

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:04.810 align:middle line:10%
Instantly, the dream transformed
and gave me a very powerful

00:58:04.810 --> 00:58:07.480 align:middle line:10%
indication about continuing
doing the work I've

00:58:07.480 --> 00:58:09.100 align:middle line:10%
been doing with veterans.

00:58:09.100 --> 00:58:11.440 align:middle line:84%
I'm working with veterans,
a lot of who are PTSD

00:58:11.440 --> 00:58:13.750 align:middle line:84%
and the PTSD nightmares
that come with them.

00:58:13.750 --> 00:58:16.000 align:middle line:84%
And this year, I realized
my biggest project this year

00:58:16.000 --> 00:58:17.590 align:middle line:90%
will be work with veterans.

00:58:17.590 --> 00:58:19.120 align:middle line:84%
And the dream is
supportive of that.

00:58:19.120 --> 00:58:21.340 align:middle line:84%
So it's give me
a whole new sense

00:58:21.340 --> 00:58:22.840 align:middle line:84%
of confidence
toward that project

00:58:22.840 --> 00:58:25.270 align:middle line:84%
that I simply didn't have
before that lucid dream.

00:58:25.270 --> 00:58:26.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:58:26.110 --> 00:58:28.930 align:middle line:84%
And you're doing a big
project in America.

00:58:28.930 --> 00:58:32.602 align:middle line:84%
Is it the Veterans
Association, or who is it with?

00:58:32.602 --> 00:58:34.060 align:middle line:84%
>>MORLEY: So the
project in America

00:58:34.060 --> 00:58:37.270 align:middle line:84%
is funded by a UK organization
called the Winston Churchill

00:58:37.270 --> 00:58:39.036 align:middle line:90%
Scholarship Foundation.

00:58:39.036 --> 00:58:40.660 align:middle line:84%
You have to apply
for all these things.

00:58:40.660 --> 00:58:42.770 align:middle line:84%
And they whittle you down to a
short list, super short list.

00:58:42.770 --> 00:58:44.390 align:middle line:84%
Then, you have an
interview process.

00:58:44.390 --> 00:58:46.420 align:middle line:84%
And I got a scholarship
to go to America

00:58:46.420 --> 00:58:50.440 align:middle line:84%
and study best practice
in mindfulness-based PTSD

00:58:50.440 --> 00:58:51.250 align:middle line:90%
treatment.

00:58:51.250 --> 00:58:52.940 align:middle line:84%
So I'll be working with
Bessel van der Kolk.

00:58:52.940 --> 00:58:54.880 align:middle line:84%
He wrote a book called
The Body Keeps the Score.

00:58:54.880 --> 00:58:56.140 align:middle line:84%
I'll be working with
Richard Miller, who

00:58:56.140 --> 00:58:57.765 align:middle line:84%
developed something
called iRest, which

00:58:57.765 --> 00:59:01.690 align:middle line:84%
is a form integrative yoga
nidra especially for trauma

00:59:01.690 --> 00:59:02.560 align:middle line:90%
survivors.

00:59:02.560 --> 00:59:04.210 align:middle line:84%
And then, I'll be
coming back to the UK

00:59:04.210 --> 00:59:08.050 align:middle line:84%
and developing a new workshop
for UK veterans and veterans'

00:59:08.050 --> 00:59:10.180 align:middle line:84%
family members, who are
just as important to work

00:59:10.180 --> 00:59:11.680 align:middle line:90%
with as the veterans themselves.

00:59:11.680 --> 00:59:13.945 align:middle line:84%
How we can use lucid dreaming
and mindfulness of dream

00:59:13.945 --> 00:59:16.900 align:middle line:84%
and sleep to help with
nightmares and PTSD.

00:59:16.900 --> 00:59:18.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Good work--

00:59:18.150 --> 00:59:20.390 align:middle line:84%
OK, we just have a
little bit of time.

00:59:20.390 --> 00:59:22.390 align:middle line:84%
So we've already said,
before you go to sleep,

00:59:22.390 --> 00:59:25.000 align:middle line:84%
you need to set the intention
that you want to have

00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:26.370 align:middle line:90%
a dream that you can recognize.

00:59:26.370 --> 00:59:28.840 align:middle line:84%
And you tell yourself
to wake up enough

00:59:28.840 --> 00:59:32.180 align:middle line:84%
at the right time to be able
to record that dream, right?

00:59:32.180 --> 00:59:32.980 align:middle line:90%
>>MORLEY: Yes.

00:59:32.980 --> 00:59:34.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Give us
the rest of the list

00:59:34.030 --> 00:59:36.430 align:middle line:84%
and also some supplements
that can help with dreaming.

00:59:36.430 --> 00:59:37.450 align:middle line:90%
>>MORLEY: Brilliant.

00:59:37.450 --> 00:59:40.870 align:middle line:10%
So yeah, those first three
things on the list I'd say--

00:59:40.870 --> 00:59:43.030 align:middle line:10%
set the intention to
remember your dreams.

00:59:43.030 --> 00:59:45.180 align:middle line:10%
Not even lucid dreams,
just normal dreams.

00:59:45.180 --> 00:59:47.560 align:middle line:10%
Then, document your
dreams in some way.

00:59:47.560 --> 00:59:49.390 align:middle line:10%
Write them down.

00:59:49.390 --> 00:59:50.290 align:middle line:90%
Draw them.

00:59:50.290 --> 00:59:51.520 align:middle line:90%
Even dance them.

00:59:51.520 --> 00:59:53.680 align:middle line:84%
Whatever you want to do
to show the dreamer--

00:59:53.680 --> 00:59:54.560 align:middle line:90%
I'm listening.

00:59:54.560 --> 00:59:57.282 align:middle line:84%
After decades of not
listening, I'm now listening.

00:59:57.282 --> 00:59:58.990 align:middle line:84%
People say-- I don't
write down my dreams

00:59:58.990 --> 01:00:00.260 align:middle line:90%
because they're so boring.

01:00:00.260 --> 01:00:02.380 align:middle line:84%
I say-- you have boring dreams
because you don't write them

01:00:02.380 --> 01:00:03.090 align:middle line:90%
down.

01:00:03.090 --> 01:00:05.048 align:middle line:84%
You need to let the
dreamer know I'm listening.

01:00:05.048 --> 01:00:06.670 align:middle line:84%
So we document our
dreams in some way.

01:00:06.670 --> 01:00:09.330 align:middle line:84%
We use our dream diaries
to spot these patterns.

01:00:09.330 --> 01:00:12.200 align:middle line:84%
Then, we set triggers that the
next time I see what I often

01:00:12.200 --> 01:00:13.060 align:middle line:90%
dream about--

01:00:13.060 --> 01:00:15.460 align:middle line:84%
my dead grandmother or
talking baby animals--

01:00:15.460 --> 01:00:17.260 align:middle line:90%
I will know that I'm dreaming.

01:00:17.260 --> 01:00:19.990 align:middle line:84%
These are our first three
steps towards lucidity.

01:00:19.990 --> 01:00:21.820 align:middle line:84%
Another thing you
can do-- very simple.

01:00:21.820 --> 01:00:25.185 align:middle line:84%
As you fall asleep tonight, in
the second half of the night

01:00:25.185 --> 01:00:27.310 align:middle line:84%
if possible-- so if you
wake up to pee in the night

01:00:27.310 --> 01:00:28.510 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

01:00:28.510 --> 01:00:31.030 align:middle line:84%
More likely to have your longer
dreams in the second half.

01:00:31.030 --> 01:00:33.820 align:middle line:84%
As you're falling back asleep
in the second half of the night,

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:36.360 align:middle line:84%
just be reciting over
and over in your mind--

01:00:36.360 --> 01:00:39.080 align:middle line:90%
tonight I recognize my dreams.

01:00:39.080 --> 01:00:41.490 align:middle line:90%
Tonight I'm lucid in my dreams.

01:00:41.490 --> 01:00:44.210 align:middle line:10%
Tonight I recognize my dreams.

01:00:44.210 --> 01:00:46.784 align:middle line:10%
Tonight I am lucid in my dreams.

01:00:46.784 --> 01:00:48.700 align:middle line:84%
When we fall asleep, we
pass through something

01:00:48.700 --> 01:00:50.689 align:middle line:90%
called the hypnogogic state.

01:00:50.689 --> 01:00:52.480 align:middle line:84%
Which, if we see from
the root of the word,

01:00:52.480 --> 01:00:54.190 align:middle line:90%
it's close to hypnosis.

01:00:54.190 --> 01:00:56.230 align:middle line:84%
It's a natural
state of hypnosis.

01:00:56.230 --> 01:00:58.120 align:middle line:84%
So if as we pass
through that, we

01:00:58.120 --> 01:01:02.200 align:middle line:84%
engage the hypnotic suggestion
to become lucid in our dreams,

01:01:02.200 --> 01:01:05.170 align:middle line:84%
we engage a very powerful
intention that may well

01:01:05.170 --> 01:01:06.810 align:middle line:90%
help us get lucid tonight.

01:01:06.810 --> 01:01:08.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

01:01:08.050 --> 01:01:10.190 align:middle line:84%
It's been an absolutely
delightful conversation.

01:01:10.190 --> 01:01:10.990 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

